Package: foundry-linux-retro-tools
Version: 1.0.1
Architecture: all
Maintainer: World Foundry <packages@worldfoundry.org>
Section: metapackages
Priority: optional
Depends: mame,
 mame-tools,
 dasm,
 cc65,
 z80dasm,
 z80asm,
 radare2,
 binwalk,
 sox,
 binutils-m68k-linux-gnu,
 xa65
Recommends: ghidra,
 f9dasm,
 vgmstream,
 libvgm
Suggests: java-common
Homepage: https://foundrylinux.org/
Description: arcade reverse-engineering and porting toolchain
 Tooling for porting classic arcade ROMs to the World Foundry engine:
 MAME (debugger + tools), 6502/Z80/68k disassemblers and assemblers,
 radare2, binwalk, sox (audio conversion), xa65 6502 cross-assembler.
 .
 Recommends includes packages we ship ourselves but haven't packaged
 yet (Ghidra repackaged from upstream, f9dasm, vgmstream, libvgm) —
 they'll move to Depends as each ships from the Foundry APT repo.
